 leads\nto an almost featureless spectrum. Helium is observed in some SLSNe after\nmaximum. The high ionization near maximum implies that both He and H may be\npresent but not observed at early times. The spectroscopic classification of\nSLSNe should probably reflect that of SNe Ib/c. Extensive time coverage is\nrequired for an accurate classification.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 1 Mar 2016 18:24:08 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-08-14"}
